@startuml use-cases-node-admin
title trawhile — Node Administration (Epic 2)

left to right direction

actor "Node Admin" as NodeAdmin

rectangle "Node Administration" {
    package "Node Tree Management" {
        usecase "View node details\nand children\n(UR-014)" as UC_ViewNode
        usecase "Create child node\n(UR-015)" as UC_CreateNode
        usecase "Edit node\n(name, description,\ncolour, icon, logo)\n(UR-016)" as UC_EditNode
        usecase "Reorder child nodes\n(UR-017)" as UC_ReorderNodes
        usecase "Deactivate node\n(UR-018)" as UC_Deactivate
        usecase "Reactivate node\n(UR-019)" as UC_Reactivate
        usecase "Move node\n(UR-020)" as UC_MoveNode
    }
    package "Node Authorizations" {
        usecase "Grant authorization\non node\n(UR-021)" as UC_GrantAuth
        usecase "Revoke authorization\nfrom node\n(UR-022)" as UC_RevokeAuth
        usecase "View node authorization\nassignments\n(UR-023)" as UC_ViewNodeAuths
    }
}

note bottom of UC_GrantAuth
  Also accessible from the user list
  (UR-009): node picker replaces
  user picker as the selection point.
  Same applies to UC_RevokeAuth.
end note

NodeAdmin --> UC_ViewNode
NodeAdmin --> UC_CreateNode
NodeAdmin --> UC_EditNode
NodeAdmin --> UC_ReorderNodes
NodeAdmin --> UC_Deactivate
NodeAdmin --> UC_Reactivate
NodeAdmin --> UC_MoveNode
NodeAdmin --> UC_GrantAuth
NodeAdmin --> UC_RevokeAuth
NodeAdmin --> UC_ViewNodeAuths

@enduml
